#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:472
#, no-wrap
msgid "Insert mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:477
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"So far, we've covered how to move around in vi, perform file i/o, and\n"
"perform basic editing operations. However, I still haven't shown you\n"
"how to actually type in free-form text! This was intentional, because\n"
"vi's insert mode is a bit complicated at first. However, after you\n"
"become comfortable with insert mode, its complexity (and flexibility)\n"
"will become an asset.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:486
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In vi <e>insert mode</e>, you'll be able to enter text directly to the screen\n"
"just like you can in many other visual editors. Once you've entered\n"
"your modifications, you can hit escape to return to <e>command mode</e>. You\n"
"can enter insert mode by pressing <c>i</c> or <c>a</c>. If you press\n"
"<c>i</c>, your text will be <e>inserted</e> before the current\n"
"character, and if you hit <c>a</c>, your text will be <e>appended</e>\n"
"after the current character. Remember, after you enter your text, hit\n"
"<c>&lt;ESC&gt;</c> to return to command mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:499
#, no-wrap
msgid "Benefits of insert mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:503
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Go ahead and try using the <c>a</c> and <c>i</c> commands. Hit either\n"
"<c>a</c> or <c>i</c>, type some text, and then hit escape to get back\n"
"to command mode. After hitting <c>a</c> or <c>i</c>, try hitting\n"
"<c>&lt;ENTER&gt;</c>, and see what happens. Try using the arrow keys\n"
"and the <c>&lt;DEL&gt;</c> key to get a feel for how insert mode\n"
"works. By using the arrow keys and <c>&lt;DEL&gt;</c> key, you can\n"
"perform significant editing steps without repeatedly entering and\n"
"leaving insert mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:516
#, no-wrap
msgid "Insert options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:520
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here are some other handy ways to enter insert mode. Press <c>A</c>\n"
"(captial) to begin appending to the <e>end</e> of the current line,\n"
"regardless of your current position on the line. Likewise, press\n"
"<c>I</c> (capital) to begin inserting text at the <e>beginning</e> of\n"
"the current line. Press <c>o</c> to create a new blank line below the\n"
"current line into which you can insert text, and press <c>O</c>\n"
"(capital) to create a new line above the current line. To replace the\n"
"entire current line with a new line, press <c>cc</c>. To replace\n"
"everything from the current position to the end of the line, type\n"
"<c>c$</c>. To replace everything from the current position to the\n"
"beginning of the line, type <c>c0</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:534
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In addition to performing a special operation, every one of these\n"
"commands will put you into insert mode. After typing in your text,\n"
"hit <c>&lt;ESC&gt;</c> to return to command mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:542
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing text"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:546
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We've used the <c>c</c> (change) command a little bit so far when we\n"
"typed <c>cc</c>, <c>c0</c> and <c>c$</c>. <c>cc</c> is a special form\n"
"of the change command, similar to <c>dd</c>. the <c>c0</c> and\n"
"<c>c$</c> commands are examples of using the change command in\n"
"combination with a movement command. In this form, <c>c</c> works\n"
"similarly to <c>d</c>, except that it leaves you in insert mode so\n"
"that you can enter replacement text for the deleted region. Try\n"
"combining some movement commands with <c>c</c> and test them out on\n"
"your file (hint: <c>cW</c>, <c>ce</c>, <c>c(</c> .)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:562
#, no-wrap
msgid "Compound Commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:567
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"vi <e>really</e> becomes powerful when you start using compound\n"
"(\"combo\") commands, like <c>d{</c> and <c>cw</c>. In addition to\n"
"these commands, you can also combine a number with any movement\n"
"command, such as <c>3w</c>, which will tell vi to jump three words to\n"
"the right. Here are some more movement \"combo\" command examples:\n"
"<c>12b</c>, <c>4j</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:576
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"vi, in addition to allowing (number)(movement command) combinations,\n"
"also allows <c>d</c> or <c>c</c> to be combined with a number or\n"
"movement command. So, <c>d3w</c> will delete the next three words,\n"
"<c>d2j</c> will delete the current and next two lines, etc. Test out\n"
"some <c>c</c> and <c>d</c> combo moves to get a feel for how powerful\n"
"and concise vi editing can be. Once these commands are second-nature,\n"
"you'll be able to edit files at blazing speed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vi-guide.xml:592
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
